    <div class="container">
        <header>
            <h1>🧪 Complete Chemistry Video Production Process</h1>
        </header>

        <div class="flowchart">
            <!-- Phase 1: Pre-production -->
            <div class="phase">
                <div class="phase-title">Phase 1: Pre-production</div>
                <div class="nodes-row">
                    <div class="node" data-target="details-1">
                        <h3>💡 Topic Selection & Literature Review</h3>
                        <p>Identify scientific questions from daily life/topics</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="node" data-target="details-2">
                        <h3>📝 Script & Storyboard</h3>
                        <p>Storyboard and script design</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="node" data-target="details-3">
                        <h3>🧪 Experiment Design</h3>
                        <p>Pilot experiments and safety assessment</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="connector"></div>

            <!-- Phase 2: Production -->
            <div class="phase">
                <div class="phase-title">Phase 2: Production</div>
                <div class="nodes-row">
                    <div class="node" data-target="details-4">
                        <h3>🎬 Live Shooting</h3>
                        <p>Capture experimental phenomena with multiple cameras</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="node" data-target="details-5">
                        <h3>📊 Data Collection</h3>
                        <p>Record raw data and phenomena</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="connector"></div>

            <!-- Phase 3: Post-production -->
            <div class="phase">
                <div class="phase-title">Phase 3: Post-production</div>
                <div class="nodes-row">
                    <div class="node" data-target="details-6">
                        <h3>✂️ Editing & Visual Effects</h3>
                        <p>Premiere + After Effects</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="node" data-target="details-7">
                        <h3>📈 Data Visualization</h3>
                        <p>Charts and animations to explain principles</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="node" data-target="details-8">
                        <h3>🔊 Voice-over & Release</h3>
                        <p>Humorous voice-over</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Details Panel -->
        <div id="details-1" class="details-panel">
            <h4>💡 Topic Selection & Literature Review</h4>
            <ul>
                <li><span class="chem-highlight">Daily Life Angle</span>: e.g., the physics/chemistry principles behind "can you eat a chip that fell on the floor?".</li>
                <li><span class="chem-highlight">Literature Review</span>: Review SCI papers to ensure scientific rigor (PhD from Tsinghua University foundation).</li>
                <li>Define the video's core argument and the "counter-intuitive" viral point.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        <div id="details-2" class="details-panel">
            <h4>📝 Script & Storyboard</h4>
            <ul>
                <li><span class="chem-highlight">Word-for-word Script</span>: Write a line-by-line script, including opening hook, principle explanation, experiment operation, and concluding insights.</li>
                <li><span class="chem-highlight">Storyboard</span>: Plan shots for each scene (close-up of reaction, wide shot of the lab bench), camera movement.</li>
                <li>Reserve insertion points for animations (to explain microscopic mechanisms).</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        <div id="details-3" class="details-panel">
            <h4>🧪 Experiment Design (Chemistry-Specific Key Points)</h4>
            <ul>
                <li><span class="chem-highlight">Pilot Experiment</span>: Small-scale trial to verify repeatability of phenomena and filming feasibility.</li>
                <li><span class="chem-highlight">Safety Assessment</span>: Assess chemical risks, prepare protective measures (fume hood, safety goggles).</li>
                <li>Equipment Preparation: High-speed camera (for fast reactions), macro lens (for crystallization).</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        <div id="details-4" class="details-panel">
            <h4>🎬 Live Shooting</h4>
            <ul>
                <li><span class="chem-highlight">Multi-Camera System</span>: Camera A for host, Camera B for overhead operation, Camera C for reaction close-ups.</li>
                <li><span class="chem-highlight">Specialized Filming</span>: High-speed photography (explosion/precipitation), time-lapse (crystal growth).</li>
                <li>Strict lighting control to avoid glare on glassware.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        <div id="details-5" class="details-panel">
            <h4>📊 Data Collection</h4>
            <ul>
                <li>Record raw data like temperature, pH, color changes.</li>
                <li>Shoot control group experiment footage.</li>
                <li>Capture ambient sounds (bubbling, combustion) for sound effects in post-production.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        <div id="details-6" class="details-panel">
            <h4>✂️ Editing & Visual Effects</h4>
            <ul>
                <li><span class="chem-highlight">Rough Cut</span>: Assemble footage according to the storyboard, control pacing.</li>
                <li><span class="chem-highlight">J-cut/L-cut</span>: Audio leading in or video leading out to enhance flow.</li>
                <li>Add particle effects (simulating molecular motion), arrow annotations.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        <div id="details-7" class="details-panel">
            <h4>📈 Data Visualization</h4>
            <ul>
                <li>Use Python/Matplotlib to generate reaction rate curve charts.</li>
                <li>3D animation to simulate chemical bond breaking/formation (Blender/C4D).</li>
                <li>Insert "soul painter"-style schematic diagrams.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        <div id="details-8" class="details-panel">
            <h4>🔊 Voice-over & Release</h4>
            <ul>
                <li><span class="chem-highlight">Voice-over</span>: Slightly faster pace, add catchphrases like "Wow" or "Incredible" to create contrast and appeal.</li>
                <li><span class="chem-highlight">Sound Effects</span>: Add funny sound effects like "Duang" to match experimental phenomena.</li>
                <li>Review subtitles (chemical formulas must be correct), publish to Bilibili.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

